description:
&lt;p&gt;The Stroke Early Supported Discharge Team in Trafford General Hospital is looking to recruit a dynamic full-time band 7 Occupational Therapist with previous experience of working within a multidisciplinary stroke team in the acute or community setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working as part of a dynamic, multidisciplinary team, alongside experienced Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists, and rehabilitation assistant staff, to provide an integrated approach to address the stroke service users’ holistic needs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Experience of working with stroke patients, and confidence in working collaboratively within a multi-disciplinary team, whilst possessing excellent clinical and communication skills are essential. The team will provide in reach and specialist rehabilitation post discharge for stroke patients of all complexity levels within a number of settings including the home environment, nursing or residential homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be treating patients on the community Stroke ESD service but may cover and support with in-patients on the Trafford General Hospital’s Stroke ward when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work 37.5 hours per week Monday – Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be self-motivated and able to work both independently and as part of a team. You will have relevant post qualification experience and should be keen to further develop your experience in Community Stroke Rehabilitation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must have the ability to travel to different geographic locations either through use of a car or access to a means of mobility to travel across the Trust footprint in line with service needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
